<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 6:00PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Macon,
northeastern Marion, northwestern Schley and southern Taylor Counties
through 645 PM EDT...
At 600 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Rupert, or near Butler,
moving south at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Butler, Reynolds, Ideal, Murrays Crossroads, Tazewell, Rupert,
Charing, Garden Valley, Hicks, Potterville, and Mauk.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
